> IMPORTANT: The sausages are cooked when they are no longer pink in the middle.
> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Preheat your oven to 200°C. Bring a large #saucepan{} of @water{} to the boil with
@salt{1/2%tsp} for the potatoes. Pop the @British Hickory Smoked Sausages{2} on
a #baking tray{} and roast on the middle shelf of your oven until golden brown
and cooked through, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, chop your @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). When
boiling add the potatoes and cook until you can easily slip a knife through,
~{15-20%minutes}. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(peeled and thinly
sliced). Trim the @spring onions{2} and thinly slice. Peel and grate the
@garlic{1%clove}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Grate the
@mature cheddar cheese{30%g} and @Monterey Jack cheese{30%g}. Drain and rinse
the @black beans{1%tin} in a #colander{}, pop half of the beans into a #bowl{}
and mash with the back of a #fork{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on a medium-high heat. When
hot add the onion to the pan and cook until soft, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add the
garlic and cook for ~{1%minute}. Pour in the @water{100%ml}, @chicken stock
paste{10%g}, @finely chopped tomatoes with onion and garlic{1%400g can} and
black beans (both whole and crushed). Stir well, then bring to a boil, lower
the heat to simmer until slightly thickened, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a colander and return to the pan, off the
heat. Add a knob of @butter{1%knob} and a splash of @?milk{} and mash with a
#potato masher{} until smooth. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and stir in
the spring onions. Cover with a #lid{} to keep warm. Once the sausages are
cooked, transfer them to a #board{} and chop them into 2cm chunks. Add them to
the tomato sauce. Increase your oven temperature to 220°C.

Stir the @BBQ sauce{64%g} through the sausage and bean mix, taste and add more
salt and pepper if needed. Transfer to an appropriately sized #oven proof dish{}
(we used a 20x20 cm for 2 people). Top with the mashed potatoes, spread to
cover the sausage mixture and sprinkle over the cheese. Cook on the top shelf
of your oven until golden and bubbling, ~{10-15%minutes}.

When the pie is ready, share between your plates and Enjoy!